<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="811" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[2012,2606,1573,2000]" lastBlockId="53.[1400,2610,2008,3461]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">
<taxonomicName box="[2013,2203,1695,1724]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="joffre">Hypsugo joffre</taxonomicName>
includes H. anthony: as a synonym, based on morphological evidence. This species has been confused with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Philetor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachypterus">Philetor brachypterus</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[2284,2358,1809,1842]" name="India" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">India</collectingCountry>
, and some specimens previously thought to represent that species actually represent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" box="[2376,2490,1888,1921]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="joffrei">H. joffrei</taxonomicName>
. The relationship ofthis species to other 
<taxonomicName box="[2495,2606,1927,1960]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hypsugo</taxonomicName>
is uncertain, and genetic data are needed for clarification. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
