<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="811" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="53.[1400,2610,2008,3461]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1403,1756,3234,3263]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List (and also listed as Data Deficient as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tate" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1787,1952,3269,3302]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anthonyi">H. anthonyi</taxonomicName>
). Joffre’s Pipistrelle is known from only a few specimens scattered over a relatively wide area. Nothing is known of its ecology and threats, and further research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
